= lesson 13: elements

Okay, for this lesson, let's take a break from grammar and instead get
philosophical!

Since ancient times, people tried to find simpler stuff that all complex stuff
consists of, or can be grouped into. The Chinese thought of wood, fire, earth,
metal, and water. The Greeks --- of fire, earth, air, and water. Some other
systems also included heaven. Even today, as science answered many questions
about the world, most things belong to one of 'four states of matter': gas,
liquid, solid, plasma.

And of course, those elements, materials, states of matter don't explain the
entirety of our complex world. But they help us make sense of it. So let's learn
some Toki Pona words that are useful for describing them:

